l stay in your office too late anymore.%0a%3c - You will stay in your office too late nowadays.%0a%3c %0a%3c Linguists assert that usage of the positive "anymore" is fairly scattered, but also somewhat clustered in the Midwest[2]. Furthermore, research suggests that this construct is of Scots-Irish origin [3].%0a%3c %0a%3c [1] https://ygdp.yale.edu/phenomena/positive-anymore%0a%3c [2] https://schwa.byu.edu/files/2014/11/F2013-Reynolds.pdf%0a%3c [3] https://twpl.library.utoronto.ca/index.php/twpl/article/download/6249/3237/%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
